29
00:02:48,584 --> 00:02:50,574
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Isn't that kinda killin' his advantage?</b></font>

30
00:02:52,784 --> 00:02:56,594
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>B-But that Eight-Six ain't exactly slow!</b></font>

31
00:02:56,594 --> 00:02:58,454
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Yeah, you're right.</b></font>

32
00:02:58,454 --> 00:03:01,364
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Maybe it's just me, but it seemed super fast...</b></font>

33
00:03:11,074 --> 00:03:13,974
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I believed he would take the starting position,</b></font>

34
00:03:13,974 --> 00:03:19,584
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>but he chose to come from behind, eh?
Impressive. A wise choice.</b></font>

35
00:03:19,584 --> 00:03:21,214
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Big brother?</b></font>

36
00:03:21,214 --> 00:03:25,984
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>You told Fujiwara something on the phone
earlier before the race started, right?</b></font>

37
00:03:25,984 --> 00:03:28,254
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>What kind of advice did you give?</b></font>

38
00:03:28,254 --> 00:03:31,554
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It was nothing that would
warrant being called "advice."</b></font>

39
00:03:31,554 --> 00:03:34,424
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I merely gave him two basic instructions.</b></font>

40
00:03:34,424 --> 00:03:36,264
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Such as?</b></font>

41
00:03:36,264 --> 00:03:41,004
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I said no matter what, do not look in the
rearview mirror till the end of the first race.</b></font>

42
00:03:41,004 --> 00:03:44,934
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The rearview mirror? In other words,
don't look behind you?</b></font>

43
00:03:48,604 --> 00:03:52,674
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="66"><b>{\an5}"Act 4: Two Pieces of Advice"</b></font>

44
00:03:59,014 --> 00:04:01,524
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Yesterday, someone said</i>
<i>that racing by outside rules</i></b></font>

45
00:04:01,524 --> 00:04:03,854
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>would be nice and fun or something.</i></b></font>

46
00:04:03,854 --> 00:04:06,764
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Shit! This is no joke!</i></b></font>

47
00:04:06,764 --> 00:04:11,334
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>At this guy's level, he could participate in</i>
<i>Toudou School races and even hold his own!</i></b></font>

48
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:14,424
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Who the hell is he?!</i></b></font>

49
00:04:21,004 --> 00:04:23,814
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I'm shocked, and not in a small way!</i></b></font>

50
00:04:23,814 --> 00:04:26,684
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>There's never been anyone who</i>
<i>could run this course a single night</i></b></font>

51
00:04:26,684 --> 00:04:31,514
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>and get to this level of mastery,</i>
<i>not even at the Toudou School!</i></b></font>

52
00:04:31,514 --> 00:04:35,684
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>What's more, I don't know what</i>
<i>kind of tuning his car's gotten,</i></b></font>

53
00:04:35,684 --> 00:04:41,684
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>but it can go up against my B16 engine,</i>
<i>and is even incredibly good at turning.</i></b></font>

54
00:04:44,134 --> 00:04:46,624
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This thing is no Eight-Six!</i></b></font>

55
00:04:47,904 --> 00:04:52,494
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>If an FR is done up this well,</i>
<i>this is the kind of race it's capable of!</i></b></font>

56
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:58,044
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>With this, they've no doubt</i></b></font>

57
00:04:58,044 --> 00:05:02,014
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>had the advantage in their traveling</i>
<i>battles, winning victory after victory...</i></b></font>

58
00:05:02,014 --> 00:05:04,984
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>But this time, they're out of luck!</i></b></font>

59
00:05:06,824 --> 00:05:11,224
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This is the home course of us, the Toudou School!</i></b></font>

60
00:05:26,204 --> 00:05:31,174
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Up till yesterday, we made a lot of
fun of our opponent's Eight-Six...</b></font>

61
00:05:31,174 --> 00:05:35,784
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>But right before the start, there was
something about him, a feeling.</b></font>

62
00:05:35,784 --> 00:05:40,354
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>That's probably why Daiki
chose to come from behind.</b></font>

63
00:05:40,354 --> 00:05:44,224
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I'm sure I would have made the same choice.</b></font>

64
00:05:44,224 --> 00:05:46,764
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I'd like to see from behind</b></font>

65
00:05:46,764 --> 00:05:51,034
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>what kind of race the "fastest
in the Gunma area" can run.</b></font>

66
00:05:51,034 --> 00:05:54,034
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If it's some lousy racing that
betrays your expectations,</b></font>

67
00:05:54,034 --> 00:05:57,034
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>you can tear out ahead and end the race.</b></font>

68
00:05:57,034 --> 00:05:59,304
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Yeah, that you could.</b></font>

69
00:05:59,304 --> 00:06:02,704
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>They say he's the best of us
currently racing, right?</b></font>

70
00:06:02,704 --> 00:06:04,314
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>What's his specialty?</b></font>

71
00:06:04,314 --> 00:06:07,574
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Daiki's good at braking.</b></font>

72
00:06:08,714 --> 00:06:12,054
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Though when you hear "braking,"
it sounds sort of bland...</b></font>

73
00:06:12,054 --> 00:06:14,824
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Nah, that ain't bland at all.</b></font>

74
00:06:14,824 --> 00:06:18,424
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>There's no better weapon
than that in the downhill!</b></font>

75
00:06:18,424 --> 00:06:23,324
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If you're a graduate of the Toudou School,
you understand why all too well.</b></font>

76
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:47,124
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>He chose to come behind for the first race?</b></font>

77
00:06:47,124 --> 00:06:49,324
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Fujiwara, listen closely.</b></font>

78
00:06:49,324 --> 00:06:53,094
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Do not look in your rearview mirror,
right up to the end of the first race.</b></font>

79
00:06:53,094 --> 00:06:56,664
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Concentrate solely on your
strategy for the course.</b></font>

80
00:06:56,664 --> 00:07:00,934
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If you run your own race,
you will not be overtaken.</b></font>

81
00:07:00,934 --> 00:07:04,274
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Listen, Fujiwara. No matter what...</b></font>

82
00:07:04,274 --> 00:07:06,294
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>...do not look behind you!</b></font>

83
00:07:12,114 --> 00:07:15,214
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I've got the general idea of what</i>
<i>that Eight-Six is capable of.</i></b></font>

84
00:07:15,214 --> 00:07:20,784
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It's better than I'd thought, but apparently</i>
<i>nothing for me to get worked up about.</i></b></font>

85
00:07:20,784 --> 00:07:22,854
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Even with the pride of</i>
<i>the Toudou School on the line,</i></b></font>

86
00:07:22,854 --> 00:07:25,324
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I want to finish this in the first race.</i></b></font>

87
00:07:26,864 --> 00:07:29,724
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I've gotta tear around him somewhere.</i></b></font>

88
00:07:29,724 --> 00:07:33,064
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I'll make my chance by putting</i>
<i>as much pressure on him as I can.</i></b></font>

89
00:07:33,064 --> 00:07:35,964
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I want to see how much he can take!</i></b></font>

90
00:07:50,984 --> 00:07:53,524
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Awesome! They're so close!</b></font>

91
00:07:53,524 --> 00:07:56,354
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Their bumpers are gonna hit!</b></font>

92
00:07:56,354 --> 00:08:02,494
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It's common knowledge now that in</i>
<i>this class, the FF is faster than the FR.</i></b></font>

93
00:08:02,494 --> 00:08:05,534
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>So this guy must have</i>
<i>the most power ful type R.</i></b></font>

94
00:08:05,534 --> 00:08:09,164
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I can't just stay behind this Eight-Six forever.</i></b></font>

95
00:08:09,164 --> 00:08:12,204
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I will definitely end this in the first race!</i></b></font>

96
00:08:12,204 --> 00:08:15,004
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The thing about braking
when going into a corner is,</b></font>

97
00:08:15,004 --> 00:08:20,274
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>what's more important isn't when you
start to brake, it's when you finish.</b></font>

98
00:08:22,684 --> 00:08:27,584
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If the point at which you finish decelerating
and start to turn is too far or too soon,</b></font>

99
00:08:27,584 --> 00:08:30,454
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>it'll result in lost time.</b></font>

100
00:08:30,454 --> 00:08:34,264
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Guys with good driving skills will
recover well and won't screw it up,</b></font>

101
00:08:34,264 --> 00:08:41,534
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>but every corner definitely has only one
ideal point for releasing the brake pedal.</b></font>

102
00:08:41,534 --> 00:08:49,574
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>That's right. Mr. Toudou is always saying that
braking is the most difficult driving skill.</b></font>

103
00:08:49,574 --> 00:08:51,074
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Of course.</b></font>

104
00:08:51,074 --> 00:08:55,314
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Daiki's assessment of that
point is always accurate.</b></font>

105
00:08:55,314 --> 00:08:59,154
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>No matter how long a braking maneuver,
the point at which he releases the pedal</b></font>

106
00:08:59,154 --> 00:09:05,254
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>is always right on the money.
It's what you call an innate sense.</b></font>

107
00:09:17,134 --> 00:09:19,804
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Daiki...</b></font>

108
00:09:19,804 --> 00:09:24,474
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>These days, ABS has become
standard in the racing world.</b></font>

109
00:09:24,474 --> 00:09:28,504
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>That's how efficient the current ABS is.</b></font>

110
00:09:32,754 --> 00:09:38,654
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>And yet, the Toudou School
has done away with ABS.</b></font>

111
00:09:38,654 --> 00:09:43,364
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>First, you gotta learn how to
brake without relying on ABS.</b></font>

112
00:09:43,364 --> 00:09:48,264
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Unless you bludgeon yourself with the
difficulty of braking till you can't stand it,</b></font>

113
00:09:48,264 --> 00:09:53,874
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>you'll never understand how to really use ABS.</b></font>

114
00:09:53,874 --> 00:09:56,634
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It's a rule of the Toudou School.</b></font>

115
00:10:23,504 --> 00:10:28,344
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This course doesn't have a center line,</i>
<i>but it's still plenty wide.</i></b></font>

116
00:10:28,344 --> 00:10:31,514
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>There are several points from</i>
<i>which I can overtake him...</i></b></font>

117
00:10:31,514 --> 00:10:33,414
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>But now what?</i></b></font>

118
00:10:33,414 --> 00:10:36,814
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I use braking to wedge myself into</i>
<i>position, but I can't quite make it.</i></b></font>

119
00:10:36,814 --> 00:10:40,544
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Who would've thought an FR's</i>
<i>corner entry could be this fast?</i></b></font>

120
00:10:52,534 --> 00:10:56,004
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It's awesome how close he's on his tail,
huh? Those are some serious skills.</b></font>

121
00:10:56,004 --> 00:11:01,044
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>No matter how ya look at it,
Ninomiya's EK is so much faster!</b></font>

122
00:11:01,044 --> 00:11:03,674
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>An Eight-Six is too slow!</b></font>

123
00:11:03,674 --> 00:11:06,374
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It's not that simple.</b></font>

124
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:10,714
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>He wouldn't stay neck-and-neck
with some slow dude, would he?</b></font>

125
00:11:10,714 --> 00:11:15,284
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Unless he really believed in that guy's skill,
he wouldn't be on his tail like that.</b></font>

126
00:11:15,284 --> 00:11:19,024
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The guy in that Eight-Six must be super fast.</b></font>

127
00:11:19,024 --> 00:11:21,524
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>--For real?!
--Yeah.</b></font>

128
00:11:21,524 --> 00:11:23,064
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Even in a race with other
students from the school,</b></font>

129
00:11:23,064 --> 00:11:26,934
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I've never seen Ninomiya get
that close to someone before.</b></font>

130
00:11:26,934 --> 00:11:31,374
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It's proof that cool, collected Ninomiya
is starting to get unusually fired up.</b></font>

131
00:11:36,204 --> 00:11:39,314
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This guy's got some serious willpower.</i></b></font>

132
00:11:39,314 --> 00:11:42,314
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>No matter how much pressure</i>
<i>I put on him, he won't budge.</i></b></font>

133
00:11:42,314 --> 00:11:47,944
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Even someone from the Toudou School</i>
<i>would surely have reacted to this by now.</i></b></font>

134
00:11:53,924 --> 00:11:56,124
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I don't have to look in the rearview mirror</i></b></font>

135
00:11:56,124 --> 00:11:59,894
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>to know he's staying right close behind me.</i></b></font>

136
00:11:59,894 --> 00:12:04,434
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I can feel the pressure on my back,</i>
<i>a prickling so sharp that it hurts.</i></b></font>

137
00:12:04,434 --> 00:12:07,344
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Still, having decided not to</i>
<i>look in the rearview mirror</i></b></font>

138
00:12:07,344 --> 00:12:10,434
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>feels strangely good, lets me concentrate.</i></b></font>

139
00:12:11,644 --> 00:12:16,344
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Ryosuke had two instructions.</i>
<i>All I have to do is follow them!</i></b></font>

140
00:12:33,334 --> 00:12:37,304
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Big brother, what's the other one?</b></font>

141
00:12:37,304 --> 00:12:40,604
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The second instruction you gave Fujiwara.</b></font>

142
00:12:40,604 --> 00:12:42,594
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The other is...</b></font>

143
00:12:44,144 --> 00:12:46,014
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>...controlled RPMs!</b></font>

144
00:12:47,544 --> 00:12:51,514
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The Eight-Six has up to 11,000 RPMs.</b></font>

145
00:12:51,514 --> 00:12:54,654
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>But I have him not using
the top-end 2,000 RPMs</b></font>

146
00:12:54,654 --> 00:12:57,354
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and shifting up when he reaches 9,000.</b></font>

147
00:12:57,354 --> 00:13:01,524
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Are you serious?! Why bother
doing something like that?</b></font>

148
00:13:01,524 --> 00:13:06,734
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Because I don't wish to show our
opponent all the cards in our hand.</b></font>

149
00:13:06,734 --> 00:13:11,004
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>As Fujiwara is not yet capable of
executing a more refined strategy...</b></font>

150
00:13:13,544 --> 00:13:15,574
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>...this was the only way I could think of</b></font>

151
00:13:15,574 --> 00:13:20,744
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>that was both simple
and would produce results.</b></font>

152
00:13:20,744 --> 00:13:26,684
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Limiting our strength against such
a powerful enemy is of course a risk,</b></font>

153
00:13:26,684 --> 00:13:29,754
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>but if Fujiwara successfully
evades him for the first race,</b></font>

154
00:13:29,754 --> 00:13:32,654
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>we can draw up a simulation
for him to win the competition.</b></font>

155
00:13:32,654 --> 00:13:35,394
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It is an enormous bet, all-or-nothing.</b></font>

156
00:13:35,394 --> 00:13:39,364
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>So he's restricting the top-end 2,000 RPMs</b></font>

157
00:13:39,364 --> 00:13:42,424
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and still outracing that
Toudou School downhiller?!</b></font>

158
00:13:45,274 --> 00:13:49,204
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>When did he acquire that level of technique?</b></font>

159
00:13:49,204 --> 00:13:51,014
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Fujiwara...</b></font>

160
00:13:51,014 --> 00:13:54,004
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>...converts all of his experiences
into self-improvement!</b></font>

161
00:14:10,294 --> 00:14:14,234
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>To that end, an exceptional degree
of concentration is required.</b></font>

162
00:14:14,234 --> 00:14:18,874
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I get it. That's why you told
him not to look behind...</b></font>

163
00:14:18,874 --> 00:14:21,374
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>So he wouldn't be rocked by
his opponent's pressure tactics</b></font>

164
00:14:21,374 --> 00:14:23,864
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and lose concentration.</b></font>

165
00:14:47,734 --> 00:14:51,604
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This isn't funny... This is bullshit!</i></b></font>

166
00:14:51,604 --> 00:14:54,174
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I didn't see this turn of events coming.</i></b></font>

167
00:14:54,174 --> 00:14:57,614
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Choosing to follow in the</i>
<i>first race was a mistake!</i></b></font>

168
00:14:57,614 --> 00:14:59,114
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It's like I...</i></b></font>

169
00:14:59,114 --> 00:15:02,344
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I'm actually havin' difficulty with this!</i></b></font>

170
00:15:24,374 --> 00:15:26,364
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>All right, here goes the second race!</b></font>

171
00:15:47,464 --> 00:15:50,694
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I had him show me plenty</i>
<i>during the first race...</i></b></font>

172
00:15:50,694 --> 00:15:54,864
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>...both the Eight-Six's racing</i>
<i>capacity and his driving skill!</i></b></font>

173
00:15:54,864 --> 00:15:57,674
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It doesn't have enough</i>
<i>speed to keep up with me.</i></b></font>

174
00:15:57,674 --> 00:15:59,504
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I'm going to finish this in a flash!</i></b></font>

175
00:16:07,914 --> 00:16:09,744
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>He's fast!</i></b></font>

176
00:16:20,364 --> 00:16:23,094
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>He's so fast. This is really bad!</i></b></font>

177
00:16:23,094 --> 00:16:26,364
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I've got no wiggle room at all...</i>
<i>I'm really at my limit!</i></b></font>

178
00:16:26,364 --> 00:16:30,104
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This is definitely at a faster</i>
<i>pace than the first race.</i></b></font>

179
00:16:30,104 --> 00:16:33,164
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Can I really even keep</i>
<i>up with him at this rate?</i></b></font>

180
00:16:36,004 --> 00:16:40,384
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Fujiwara will expend considerable powers
of concentration when coming from behind.</b></font>

181
00:16:40,384 --> 00:16:45,614
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>His senses are such that he will be able to
deal with speeds he has never experienced.</b></font>

182
00:16:45,614 --> 00:16:47,554
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>He should be able to keep up.</b></font>

183
00:16:49,454 --> 00:16:52,424
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>In the course of being dragged along
by a local racer faster than himself,</b></font>

184
00:16:52,424 --> 00:16:55,554
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>he will make his enemy's speed
completely and utterly his own.</b></font>

185
00:17:02,304 --> 00:17:07,564
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If things proceed according to my simulation,
he will overtake the racer from Toudou School.</b></font>

186
00:17:10,204 --> 00:17:14,374
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I'm counting on you, Fujiwara.</i>
<i>Rely on your senses!</i></b></font>

187
00:17:35,564 --> 00:17:37,734
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>What's going on?!</i></b></font>

188
00:17:37,734 --> 00:17:42,304
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I should have a clear idea of his</i>
<i>max speed from the first race!</i></b></font>

189
00:17:42,304 --> 00:17:45,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>But he's definitely racing</i>
<i>above that speed now!</i></b></font>

190
00:17:45,844 --> 00:17:47,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>There's no way he should be able to keep up!</i></b></font>

191
00:17:47,844 --> 00:17:49,644
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>So what's he doing there?!</i></b></font>

192
00:17:51,454 --> 00:17:52,914
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I'm scared!</i></b></font>

193
00:17:52,914 --> 00:17:56,824
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Up till now, I've never thought that</i>
<i>doing the downhill could be this scary.</i></b></font>

194
00:17:56,824 --> 00:17:59,624
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>If I let off the gas, it'll all be over.</i></b></font>

195
00:17:59,624 --> 00:18:02,324
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It would be easy...</i></b></font>

196
00:18:02,324 --> 00:18:06,324
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>But the other part of me is saying,</i>
<i>"Don't you dare let off!"</i></b></font>

197
00:18:11,934 --> 00:18:14,944
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Is that for real?!</b></font>

198
00:18:14,944 --> 00:18:16,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>All right.</b></font>

199
00:18:16,844 --> 00:18:19,044
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I just heard from the guys at the first hairpin,</b></font>

200
00:18:19,044 --> 00:18:21,784
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and it looks like there's no space
at all between the two cars.</b></font>

201
00:18:21,784 --> 00:18:25,144
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>What does that mean?! This is bad.</b></font>

202
00:18:50,714 --> 00:18:52,214
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I can't shake him off!</i></b></font>

203
00:18:52,214 --> 00:18:55,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This is at a much faster pace than the</i>
<i>first race, but he's keeping right up!</i></b></font>

204
00:18:58,584 --> 00:19:01,484
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If Fujiwara can keep up in this second race,</b></font>

205
00:19:01,484 --> 00:19:05,524
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>a certain advantageous element will
present itself as he enters the second half.</b></font>

206
00:19:05,524 --> 00:19:07,364
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Do you know what that is?</b></font>

207
00:19:07,364 --> 00:19:12,094
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Uh, no. I don't have a clue.</b></font>

208
00:19:12,094 --> 00:19:13,564
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>And you, Keisuke?</b></font>

209
00:19:13,564 --> 00:19:16,434
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I get it, for the most part.</b></font>

210
00:19:16,434 --> 00:19:18,604
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It's the difference in drive systems, right?</b></font>

211
00:19:18,604 --> 00:19:23,004
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>With the FR, the rear tires do
the job of accelerating the car...</b></font>

212
00:19:26,274 --> 00:19:28,414
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>But in the FF's case, in corner entries</b></font>

213
00:19:28,414 --> 00:19:32,244
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and also when it accelerates,
only the front tires get worked.</b></font>

214
00:19:34,384 --> 00:19:38,394
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>A downhill attack places load on
front tires that are already taxed.</b></font>

215
00:19:38,394 --> 00:19:42,594
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The tires of the front-wheel drive
EK-9 will start feeling the strain first.</b></font>

216
00:19:46,694 --> 00:19:48,294
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Dammit!</i></b></font>

217
00:19:52,904 --> 00:19:56,904
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Unbelievable! I thought I could</i>
<i>settle this in the first race</i></b></font>

218
00:19:56,904 --> 00:19:59,814
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>and pushed my car too hard</i>
<i>along unreasonable angles!</i></b></font>

219
00:19:59,814 --> 00:20:01,644
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>That was an incredible mistake.</i></b></font>

220
00:20:01,644 --> 00:20:05,414
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It's put excess strain on the tires.</i></b></font>

221
00:20:05,414 --> 00:20:08,924
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The RPM limitation was a confusion tactic.</b></font>

222
00:20:08,924 --> 00:20:12,824
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>A driver of that caliber would be able
to accurately grasp the capabilities</b></font>

223
00:20:12,824 --> 00:20:15,164
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>of the car driving ahead of him--</b></font>

224
00:20:15,164 --> 00:20:17,494
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>in other words,
determine he could overtake it</b></font>

225
00:20:17,494 --> 00:20:19,564
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and plan a short, decisive battle.</b></font>

226
00:20:19,564 --> 00:20:23,464
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>So you wanted to put added
wear on his tires and brakes?</b></font>

227
00:20:23,464 --> 00:20:25,304
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>That's incredible, bro.</b></font>

228
00:20:25,304 --> 00:20:29,474
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>To think that those two pieces of
advice had such deep thought to them...</b></font>

229
00:20:29,474 --> 00:20:32,144
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The important part is yet to come.</b></font>

230
00:20:32,144 --> 00:20:35,084
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The Eight-Six's tires can't
hold out that long either.</b></font>

231
00:20:35,084 --> 00:20:36,914
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It's unknown whether he can make use of</b></font>

232
00:20:36,914 --> 00:20:39,814
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>the slight chance he has been given.</b></font>

233
00:20:51,594 --> 00:20:53,864
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It's not just my imagination.</i></b></font>

234
00:20:53,864 --> 00:20:57,634
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>His corner entry has suddenly gotten sloppier.</i></b></font>

235
00:20:57,634 --> 00:20:59,634
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>His tires?</i></b></font>

236
00:20:59,634 --> 00:21:06,314
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>The tires are causing heat shear...</i>
<i>but mine still have strength left in them!</i></b></font>

237
00:21:06,314 --> 00:21:12,374
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I can tear past this fast EK and end the race!</i></b></font>

238
00:21:14,484 --> 00:21:18,994
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If it were you, where would you start looking
for the point to strike in this situation?</b></font>

239
00:21:18,994 --> 00:21:22,794
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>On any mountain pass, the more you
run it, the more there will be points</b></font>

240
00:21:22,794 --> 00:21:25,734
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>where the gear ratio simply will not match.</b></font>

241
00:21:25,734 --> 00:21:29,504
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>For example, a point where,
as you accelerate toward a corner,</b></font>

242
00:21:29,504 --> 00:21:33,204
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>you waver between shifting up or not.</b></font>

243
00:21:33,204 --> 00:21:37,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I get that much, but what if your
tachometer's in the red zone,</b></font>

244
00:21:37,844 --> 00:21:42,244
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>but you don't have enough room
to shift gears and accelerate?</b></font>

245
00:21:42,244 --> 00:21:46,914
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>In cases like that, you do nothing
and just grin and bear it, right?</b></font>

246
00:21:46,914 --> 00:21:49,684
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>That sure is terrible.</b></font>

247
00:21:49,684 --> 00:21:54,494
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It's like your hands are tied,
unable to speed up or slow down, huh?</b></font>

248
00:21:54,494 --> 00:21:57,264
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Oh! So that's it!</b></font>

249
00:21:57,264 --> 00:21:59,424
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I've got it!</b></font>

250
00:22:00,534 --> 00:22:05,264
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The Eight-Six's engine has
more RPMs than the EK9's!</b></font>

251
00:22:06,934 --> 00:22:09,434
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>That engine's got some
kind of ace up its sleeve.</b></font>

252
00:22:15,844 --> 00:22:19,114
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Advising him to rein in
the top-end 2,000 RPMs</b></font>

253
00:22:19,114 --> 00:22:22,854
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and not showing them to the opponent...</b></font>

254
00:22:22,854 --> 00:22:24,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>That was the real objective!</b></font>

255
00:22:28,194 --> 00:22:29,894
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>What?!</i></b></font>

256
00:23:01,394 --> 00:23:02,924
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>He passed me!</i></b></font>

257
00:23:02,924 --> 00:23:05,834
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Braking is my specialty, but...</i></b></font>

258
00:23:05,834 --> 00:23:09,924
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>...it let him pass me!</i></b></font>

259
00:23:39,194 --> 00:23:40,934
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Daiki...</b></font>

260
00:23:40,934 --> 00:23:43,534
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I'm sorry. He beat me.</b></font>

261
00:23:43,534 --> 00:23:46,804
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>What the hell's going on?! I don't believe it!</b></font>

262
00:23:46,804 --> 00:23:49,364
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>You, a local, lost?</b></font>

263
00:23:54,684 --> 00:23:59,274
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Well done, Fujiwara. You really did a good job.</b></font>

264
00:24:12,294 --> 00:24:17,364
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I'm glad. I got so worked up that</i>
<i>I'm dripping with cold sweat...</i></b></font>

265
00:24:17,364 --> 00:24:20,634
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Ryosuke almost never makes that sort of face.</i></b></font>

266
00:24:20,634 --> 00:24:24,044
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I was able to follow through</i>
<i>with what Ryosuke had hoped.</i></b></font>

267
00:24:26,544 --> 00:24:29,144
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>And I'm glad. I really am.</i></b></font>

268
00:24:42,494 --> 00:24:45,194
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Please do your best, Keisuke.</b></font>

269
00:24:46,734 --> 00:24:51,934
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Of course I will. I'm going on the</i>
<i>attack, right from the first race.</i></b></font>

270
00:25:12,054 --> 00:25:14,784
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>All right, now beginning the hill climb!</b></font>

271
00:25:46,754 --> 00:25:48,764
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Hey sanjou, new generation</i></b></font>

272
00:25:48,764 --> 00:25:51,664
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Atarashii jidai tourai o ima teishou</i></b></font>

273
00:25:51,664 --> 00:25:56,804
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Itsu made wasureta furi o shiteiru no?</i></b></font>

274
00:25:56,804 --> 00:26:01,904
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>(Chigiresou na heart no tension) Mune no uzuki</i></b></font>

275
00:26:01,904 --> 00:26:06,914
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Sono hitomi no oku, osaekirenai mono</i></b></font>

276
00:26:06,914 --> 00:26:12,354
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>(Sou matowaritsuku kono image) yoru o niramu</i></b></font>

277
00:26:12,354 --> 00:26:22,194
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Sou dare no kokoro ni te o</i>
<i>nobashite fureru subemo</i></b></font>

278
00:26:22,194 --> 00:26:27,134
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>shiranakatta futari, mou koko kara</i></b></font>

279
00:26:27,134 --> 00:26:32,274
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>(Hey sanjou new generation,</i>
